Text.Value: Not sure the world's ready for unleashed Karlach, but it's getting it anyway. Thanks to Dammon. Thanks to you. Thanks to fate.
I try not to think about it. I still think about it constantly, but, you know, I try.
I was hoping you'd say that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sweetly, in response to 'let's meet up later'

Text.Value: How do you like the upgrade to your engine?
Hopefully it'll hold together long enough to get tuned up.
What'll you do with your newfound freedom?
What does that infernal engine do to you?
Change the subject.
I liked the look of it.
The year? Ten ere. The place? A sleepy little town called Baldur's Gate. Our hero? Karlach, a knock-kneed delinquent from the Outer City with everything to give and nothing to lose.

EditorData.NodeContext: Like she's an old timey radio announcer teeing up a story

Text.Value: Guy named Gortash. Politician. Inventor. One of these wheeler-dealer types who seems to have a finger in every pie.
Help me kill those Paladins of Tyr, and I'll tell you. A bit of good gossip for your good help.
High pain tolerance. And a dynamic duo of truly shitty bosses.
Thanks to you, I'll live to fight another day. And get this bloody thing tuned up.
Wild, right? And believe it or not, I'm one of Zariel's least-mutilated pets.
When I touched you, I felt like... a real person.

EditorData.NodeContext: Platonic touch

Text.Value: But it's a bit early in the game to be getting into tragic backstories. Let's save the scar-show for later, after we've worked up an appetite for tragedy.

EditorData.logicalname: Knows the story of the engine

Text.Value: The world's my funhouse.

EditorData.NodeContext: Maybe: Waggling fingers like she's gonna go around touching stuff.

Text.Value: I'm very glad you got what you wanted.
Let's go find your friend before I blow a gasket. Lead on!
Slightly mad, to be honest. Are you all right?
Let's hope Dammon is as good as he seems. Once my engine's handled, I can focus on more important matters - tadpoles, cults, frosty pints...
Granted the fire lasted a little longer than it should.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Note to cinematic artist: No cue for being on fire.

Text.Value: I wouldn't mind that myself. I've never been one for too much contact.
Leave.
I can be close to you now. Without fear. Without thinking too hard. We can just... be.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's pleased her engine is fixed.

Text.Value: The two of them conspired to give me a little gift.
Sometimes I'm jealous of that girl. Ugh, to feel so invincible again.
But hey. That's life. Or so I'm told.
Sharp instincts, sharp weapons, and a knack for improvisation. That's the only way to survive 'em.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player has asked Karlach about how to kill demons/ devils, and though she hated fighting for Zariel, she's a master of martial prowess and loves talking about her techniques. In these nodes, it's like someone has asked her about her special interest hobby and she's really into explaining the nuances.

Text.Value: When you hugged me, I felt warm inside... not hot, not burning. Warm and light. I was so happy.
You've never met anyone so desperate for a hug as this one right here. Pathetic, perhaps, but true. It's my lot to bear, and I bear it badly.

EditorData.NodeContext: Light in tone, this shouldn't be too down-beat, though she is sincere.

Text.Value: Ugh, I don't want to think about that now.
What does the engine allow you to do?
What's that been like?
You've earned it, after all you've endured.
You... did? Wow. That was sound of you. Why'd you do it?

EditorData.NodeContext: Wanting to accept the favor but experience has made her wary of trusting (this is early in her relationship to the player)

Text.Value: Does it always last that long?
What'll happen if you don't get tuned up?
They were agents of a devil. I wasn't going to let them roam the area unchallenged.
You're my kind of people.
Anyway, what were we talking about?

EditorData.NodeContext: Suddenly snapping out of explaining how to kill demons, realizing she was getting really into it, and coming back down to earth as it were.

Text.Value: I'll keep an eye out for someone like that.
Felt good letting off a little steam after facing off with this ignots.

EditorData.NodeContext: IG-not, a Karlach-specific swear meaning 'foolish person'
EditorData.logicalname: IPRD - KAR NOT BURNING - AFTER ENRAGE AT TOLLHOUSE

Text.Value: I don't want to think about that now. I want to think about now. I'm so happy. That's all I need to know.

EditorData.NodeContext: The repetition of now/now is intentional - she's stumbling over her words a tiny bit. She's just excited and trying to make sense of things.

Text.Value: Agonising! Gods! What I wouldn't give for a hug. A pat! Anything!

EditorData.NodeContext: Light in tone, this shouldn't be too down-beat, though she is sincere.

Text.Value: Let's move, eh? I'm running high and in the mood for a fight.
Ah well. Can't have it all, can you. Not today, at least.
Leave.
How did you end up with such a contraption in your chest?
I'm just happy to know someone can do something about this little situation. Thought I was alone but I'm not, am I?
With your help - and Dammon's - I might be able to get a little more control over this thing. None too soon either - it's starting to wear me out a bit.
Who knows! Maybe I can run like this indefinitely. But... maybe not.
I'm always keen for a good fight.
Maybe even manage a pat or bump without burning someone to death. It's been a long time.
Granted the fire lasted a little longer than it should.
Hear that? Infernal engine for a heart. Lets me burn as hot as the Hells. Seems to be running in overdrive since I left Avernus.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
"Hear that?"
She thumps her left chest with right hand, like pounding a car hood. Something mechanic clangs within.
(etc.)
EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Karlach fist thumping chest (metalic sounds), metal clang (inside body, muffled)

Text.Value: When you kissed me, I was... I don't know if I have the words.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blissful

Text.Value: One of these days I'll sort the whole infernal affair out, get myself cooled off, and start making up for lost time.
Sounds like a good lead. Hopefully, our guy will be among them. A tune-up would do this old tub a world of good.
No more than anyone else. Well. Maybe slightly more. But that's the past now. I'm free. More free than I've ever been, now.
You mentioned a boss who gave you up to Zariel. Who was it?
Leave.
So not only do you have this thing in your chest, but it's burning up?
I'll tell you all about it, after we've taken down those 'paladins' I'm after. Believe me - it's worth the wait.
Like you should've melted a long time ago. How can you stand it?
It's a long story. But a good one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Being a little deadpan here. She's about to tell the story of her heart being replaced. Feed into the 'The year? Ten ere.' line.

Text.Value: Go on, then. Tell them.
You got your second upgrade. How does it feel?
Engine heats up the whole system enough not to get burned. Hopefully it'll hold together long enough to get tuned up.
I'll mete out the best ones, bit by bit, so you always have a reason to keep me around. Clever, right?

EditorData.NodeContext: Being cheeky.

Text.Value: Nope. Not sure how good it is for the gears, either.
TOUCH! Touch everything. Touch everyone that'll let me. Shake hands. Dance a waltz. Maybe even kiss a face or two, if I find a good candidate.
I was a kid looking for a way to fill my days and make some cash when I fell into the wrong crowd. Worked for a guy I respected. A lot. Turns out the feeling wasn't mutual.

EditorData.NodeContext: Laughs, brings the story back to reality.

Text.Value: Demons, on the other hand - every demon is absolutely singular. You can't ever think you've got 'em typed out.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player has asked Karlach about how to kill demons/ devils, and though she hated fighting for Zariel, she's a master of martial prowess and loves talking about her techniques. In these nodes, it's like someone has asked her about her special interest hobby and she's really into explaining the nuances.

Text.Value: Glad to be counted among them. Really glad.
How could you withstand the heat?
That's the short of it. Bloody thing's been in overdrive since I left Avernus.
Gives me energy. Power. But you've seen it in action - very hard to control.
Granted the fire's lasting a little longer than it should. How do I look?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little nervous but  trying not to show it.

Text.Value: You must be... pent up.
Honey, I could go all night.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: After her line, she shudders and shakes herself off. The flames die down and vanish.

Text.Value: Me too, soldier. Gods! Me too. For every knock we take, I feel like I get a little treat just to keep me going.
Who, me? This is the best day I've had in years.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: After her line, she shudders and shakes herself off. The flames die down and vanish.

Text.Value: Well now! Maybe I could make his acquaintance? A tightened screw or two might let me keep a little calmer.
I've never been more excited for anything in my life.
Leave.
When you put your hand on me, I was finally a closed circuit. Complete.
Then again, facing 'em down might've put my tin can into overdrive.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's about to explain her infernal heart for the first time.

Text.Value: Looks like Soul Coins are really feeding your engine's fire.
You have a mechanic for your heart?
Misery always overstays its welcome. And joy leaves too soon. I'll cry later, but not now.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little low, a litlte vulnerable. She knows she's gonna have to deal with hard truths later, but right now she just wants to shake hands with the world.

Text.Value: I always take care of my people.
There are some tieflings holed up in a druid's grove nearby. We might look there.
In your expert opinion, what's the best way to kill a devil?
If I'm excited at all - angry, nervous, delighted, enticed... I burn hot. Hot enough to burn anyone who gets close.

EditorData.NodeContext: On 'enticed' she's saying if she gets turned on, the flames start to go nuts.

Text.Value: Had to let off a little steam after facing off with those ignots.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Note to cinematic artist: Add cue for her to be burning
EditorData.NodeContext: IG-not, a Karlach-specific word for 'foolish person'

Text.Value: Depends on the type. Ice devils hate an inferno, but that's an easy one. Orthons love projectiles - what they don't love is getting their bombs lobbed right back in their faces.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player has asked Karlach about how to kill demons/ devils, and though she hated fighting for Zariel, she's a master of martial prowess and loves talking about her techniques. In these nodes, it's like someone has asked her about her special interest hobby and she's really into explaining the nuances.

Text.Value: Ten years of that. The stories I could tell.
Wish I could've been there to watch those ignots crumble, but I'm just happy they're off my tail.

EditorData.NodeContext: Her word for 'idiots'. IG-not.

Text.Value: I don't have to hold back.
I'd trade you if I could. I miss it more than anything.
I guess I was naive to think everything he got up to was above board. What did I know? I saw a job - a good job - with people I liked doing work I was good at.
Through the jigs and the reels, he made a deal with Zariel behind my back. You know Zariel, right? Archdevil of Avernus?
My heart was racing, but I didn't hurt you. I don't have to be afraid of myself anymore.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not a romance branch, she's just getting into her metaphor. She's talking about getting her engine fixes and being able to touch people.

Text.Value: A weaponsmith, huh? Not sure if he's the guy, but I'd love to find out. A tune-up would do this rusty heart a world of good.
Old Rusty? Sure.
Incredible. Like I'm really alive. Like we can finally be real.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost giddy. She just got her engine fixed with the 2nd upgrade.

Text.Value: The first time I faced down those 'paladins,' they let slip there was an infernal mechanic in the area. A tiefling. He might be able to stabilise things - if I can find him.
Hot.
Phew. Had to let off a little steam after facing off with those ignots.

EditorData.NodeContext: IG-not, a Karlach-specific swear meaning 'foolish person'
EditorData.logicalname: IPRD - KAR BURNING - AFTER ENRAGE AT TOLLHOUSE

Text.Value: Why not. Let me see if I can paint you a picture.
Granted the fire's lasting a little longer than it should. How do I look?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little nervous but  trying not to show it.

Text.Value: Won't be seeing my mechanic any time soon, so I'll just make the most of the extra heat. Just don't get too close 'til I've found a way to calm it down.
Careful, soldier. If I burn any hotter, I might explode.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: After her line, she shudders and shakes herself off. The flames die down and vanish.

Text.Value: What about what Dammon said? About how your engine won't survive in the material plane?
Thanking you. A tune-up would give this rustbox of mine a new lease on life.
Burn, baby. As hot as I can tolerate. Makes me a beast in battle. Hardly remember what I was like before it.
But! Not today.
Like I got something back - something I've wanted for a really long time.
How the hells did you get an infernal engine for a heart?
What about what Dammon said? About how your engine won't survive in the material plane?
Meanwhile, I'll need to find someone who can tune up my engine sooner rather than later. Believe me when I say this thing is hot.
Incredible, right? Keep 'em coming. I can handle it.
It sounds like all we need to do to fix your engine is find some infernal iron.

EditorData.logicalname: Knows the story of the engine

Text.Value: She put this thing in my chest and set me to work. Well, to war. I learned quick how to stay alive. And the engine served me when it came to killing devils.
Same. Wish you would've brought me along for the ride, but I'm just happy those ignots are off my tail.
Wonder if they meant Dammon - a tiefling weaponsmith.
I met someone who might be able to help - a smith who worked in the Hells for a time.
Leave.
What about it? Had to let off a little steam after facing off with those ignots.
